  Q. What are your thoughts now about the TV remark, was it something off-the-cuff? Have you had time to think about it.   
 PAUL PIERCE: Say that again?   
  
  Q. The remarks you made after the game, was that an off-the-cuff thing? If you had to do it again, would you? Was it not a big deal?   
 PAUL PIERCE: It wasn't a big deal to me. I'm just saying I want us to go home, I want our crowd to be ready, I want us to play our best, and I want to win two games.   
  
