 PAUL PIERCE: I don't know. You guys know more than that. Break out the brooms. I'm not going to say that on the tape. That's pretty unprofessional. I was probably talking trash on the court that I wouldn't say here. I definitely wouldn't say that.   
  
  Q. Breaking down the defense, how important is it not letting them get inside and --  
 PAUL PIERCE: I think our defense has been spectacular. That's a big part of the game. Dwight rolling to the basket. Doing a good job pressuring the ball. That's the biggest play in everybody's playbook. When we defend that well, I think we've been doing a good job.   
  
  Q. Is Kevin at this point back from the injury and getting on a roll --  
